race.comment: WALSH BAY (3) had put six wins together on the bounce before just missing the frame last time out around this circuit. Grows a leg for hoop Thornton who has five wins from just six rides and a return to winning ways would not surprise. TEXAS FIREBALL (10) has been right there in all three runs this campaign and looks to be building up to another victory. Maps ideally for this from gate two and can make his presence felt. KALUAKOI (7) was a touch disappointing at the latest effort but the form prior was good enough for a race of this calibre. Worth another chance. SIBAAQ (1) got the job done here at the latest effort and winning rider Franklin stays on top. May have turned the corner now. SUN WORSHIPPER (9) rounds out the selections in a race with only a handful of chances.
